snippet.textDisplay:
0:05 Why would he have to escape? He is better guarded in prison(from rivals/etc) and can likely influence his gang from inside like many other criminals.
-----------------------------------------------
0:55 Misleading....those "massive" tunnels have been documented and are much smaller than people think.
--------------------------------------------------
4:35 Life PLUS 30 years? What, will they dig him up and make his body stick around for 3 more decades?
--------------------------------------------------
5:15 I think criminals should be punished and all, but keeping them away from anyone for 23 hours a day while knowing what happens when people are kept isolated for so long.....to me that seems a bit inhumane, even for the worst of the worst.
-------------------------------------------------
8:10 No tv but religious programs or educational television? What, is this the early prison days?
---------------------------------------------------
9:45 I'm not familiar with the prison system, but i'm going to guess that shackling people during a fire/etc is not allowed per safety regulations.
